21 SECTION 1. DO NOT CODIFY. Legislative findings and intent.
22 (a) The General Assembly finds that:
23 (1) Preschool is an essential resource and component in the
24 State of Arkansas that is necessary to prepare young children to adequately
25 participate in a learning environment in elementary education;
26 (2) Currently, the Arkansas Better Chance Program and Arkansas
27 Better Chance for School Success Program have twenty-three thousand (23,000)
28 available preschool slots between the two programs;
29 (3) It is in the best interest of Arkansas's families and
30 childcare providers to combine the Arkansas Better Chance Program and
31 Arkansas Better Chance for School Success Program to promote efficiency in
32 the use and administration of the programs; and
33 (4) The qualifications for eligibility to participate in the
34 Arkansas Better Chance Program and Arkansas Better Chance for School Success
35 Program should be established by the Division of Elementary and Secondary
36 Education and should be the same qualifications for eligibility to
